      "contentFieldValue": {
        "data": "<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">\n  <strong>Note:</strong> please note that Liferay has renamed its Liferay Experience\n  Could offerings to <i><strong>Liferay SaaS</strong></i> (formerly LXC) and\n  <i><strong>Liferay PaaS</strong></i> (formerly LXC-SM).\n</div>\n<p><strong>Published February 26, 2024</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-red110\"><strong>Updated May 31, 2024: </strong>On Monday, <strong>July 1st</strong> Elasticsearch images below 7.17.13 or 8.9.2 will no longer be deployable</span></p>\n<h1 id=\"h_01HQ6CSTS871N5ECAR0ARCFYG5\">Summary</h1>\n<p>Liferay currently supports and provides Elasticsearch images for versions 6, 7, and 8 for the purposes of deployment on our cloud platform. Due to over 17 critical vulnerabilities identified in various <a href=\"https://hub.docker.com/_/elasticsearch/tags?page=1&amp;name=6.8\">Elasticsearch 6.8.x images</a> on which liferaycloud/elasticsearch:6.8.x images are based, Liferay will be discontinuing support for Elasticsearch 6 on our cloud platform.</p>\n<h1 id=\"h_01HQ6DRVY5F0P7KEDKRAYA1C7A\">Details</h1>\n<p>What does this mean for you?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No new Elasticsearch 6 images will be produced by Liferay</li>\n<li>Elasticsearch 6 images should no longer be used on Liferay’s cloud platform</li>\n<li>If a ticket is opened relating to an issue with Elasticsearch 6, Liferay Support will first ask you to update to version 7.17.13 or 8.9.2 before providing further assistance</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"h_01HQ6DV873QDHT3B7XNXV9TEFS\">Resolution</h1>\n<p>In order to avoid disruptions or downtime, all Liferay PaaS customers must update to Elasticsearch 7.17.13 or 8.9.2 and above. If the update is not complete by the date outlined below, <strong>environments still running Elasticsearch 6 may experience reduced functionality, deployment failures, or downtime</strong>.<br><br>Here is a breakdown of the updates needed based on your current Liferay DXP version:</p>\n<table style=\"height: 132px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 22px; width: 141px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\"><strong>Liferay Version</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height: 22px; width: 141px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\"><strong>Minimum DXP Update</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height: 22px; width: 141px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\"><strong>Minimum Elasticsearch Update</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 88px; width: 280px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\">DXP Quarterly Release, 7.4, 7.3</td>\n<td style=\"height: 88px; width: 280px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\">No DXP update required</td>\n<td style=\"height: 88px; width: 280px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\">No Elasticsearch update required</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 88px; width: 280px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\">7.2 ≥ Fix Pack 12</td>\n<td style=\"height: 88px; width: 280px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\">No DXP update required</td>\n<td style=\"height: 88px; width: 280px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\" rowspan=\"4\">liferaycloud/elasticsearch:7.17.13-5.2.0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 88px; width: 280px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\">7.2 &lt; Fix Pack 12</td>\n<td style=\"height: 88px; width: 280px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\">7.2 Fix Pack 12</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 88px; width: 280px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\">7.1 ≥ Fix Pack 23</td>\n<td style=\"height: 88px; width: 280px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\">No DXP update required</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 22px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 88px; width: 280px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\">7.1 &lt; Fix Pack 23</td>\n<td style=\"height: 88px; width: 280px; background-color: #f7f8f9;\">7.1 Fix Pack 23</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<aside class=\"alert alert-info\"><span class=\"wysiwyg-font-size-large\"><strong>Note</strong>: We recommend updating to the latest DXP Quarterly Release and <a href=\"https://support.liferay.com/02-15-2024-service-release-updates\">liferaycloud/elasticsearch:8.9.2-5.2.1</a>. If you choose to update to Elasticsearch 7.17+, we recommend using the latest available version on our <a href=\"https://help.liferay.com/hc/en-us/sections/360006251311-Services-Changelog\">Services Changelog</a> page. </span></aside>\n<h1 id=\"h_01HQ6DVE3N7AKYWH4E68WPD0A2\">Timeline</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>March 1, 2024</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Elasticsearch 6 images will no longer be supported</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strike> <strong>May 1, 2024 </strong> </strike><strong> July 1, 2024</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Elasticsearch images below 7.17.13 or 8.9.2 will no longer be deployable</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"h_01HQ6EJD8SFZJFM37KSDXKRK0Y\">Additional Information</h1>\n<p>If you encounter any issues or have questions about these changes, please <a href=\"https://help.liferay.com/hc/requests/new\">submit a ticket</a> and Liferay Support will be happy to assist.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.liferay.com/upgrading-elasticsearch-on-liferay-paas\">Upgrading Elasticsearch on Liferay PaaS</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.liferay.com/elastic-stack-and-liferay-enterprise-search-security-advisory-cve-2023-31418-cve-2023-31419-cve-2023-31422\">Elastic Stack and Liferay Enterprise Search Security Advisory</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://support.liferay.com/search-engine-compatibility-matrix\">Search Engine Compatibility Matrix</a></li>\n</ul>"
      },
